rComments: The prof does not give us any material to study for the midterm test which is 50%of the grade btw. The only thing we can study from is the lecture slides which is pretty dense on its own.
She's enthusiastic about what she teaches and it shows. A very caring and intelligent professor. Do yourself a favour and take her classes!
Really engaging, smart, and easy to talk to. Definitely worth visiting for a chat during office hours.
Intriguing topic for an art history course and overall very easy to digest the course content!

This course reviews all of the basic paintings and monuments you probably already learned from your 100-level art history courses. The textbook is thin, easy to read and full of pictures. Her lectures come directly from the textbook, so there are no surprises. She has a heavy accent but overall she is helpful and patient.
Friendly prof, well organized, gives extensive feedback. Very interesting selection of articles to read.
